{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1387,"text":"I am a palliative care physician"},{"time":2936,"text":"and I would like to talk to you\ntoday about health care."},{"time":6393,"text":"I'd like to talk to you\nabout the health and care"},{"time":10917,"text":"of the most vulnerable\npopulation in our country --"},{"time":13788,"text":"those people dealing with the most\ncomplex serious health issues."},{"time":20202,"text":"I'd like to talk to you\nabout economics as well."},{"time":23028,"text":"And the intersection of these two\nshould scare the hell out of you --"},{"time":27508,"text":"it scares the hell out of me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":30199,"text":"I'd also like to talk to you\nabout palliative medicine:"},{"time":33835,"text":"a paradigm of care for this population,\ngrounded in what they value."},{"time":40544,"text":"Patient-centric care based on their values"},{"time":43765,"text":"that helps this population\nlive better and longer."},{"time":48458,"text":"It's a care model that tells the truth"},{"time":51744,"text":"and engages one-on-one"},{"time":53008,"text":"and meets people where they're at."}]},{"cues":[{"time":57460,"text":"I'd like to start by telling the story\nof my very first patient."},{"time":61247,"text":"It was my first day as a physician,"},{"time":63307,"text":"with the long white coat ..."},{"time":65519,"text":"I stumbled into the hospital"},{"time":67025,"text":"and right away there's a gentleman,\nHarold, 68 years old,"},{"time":69849,"text":"came to the emergency department."},{"time":71474,"text":"He had had headaches for about six weeks"},{"time":73481,"text":"that got worse and worse\nand worse and worse."},{"time":76460,"text":"Evaluation revealed he had cancer\nthat had spread to his brain."},{"time":81148,"text":"The attending physician directed me\nto go share with Harold and his family"},{"time":87791,"text":"the diagnosis, the prognosis\nand options of care."}]},{"cues":[{"time":92114,"text":"Five hours into my new career,"},{"time":95092,"text":"I did the only thing I knew how."},{"time":97922,"text":"I walked in,"},{"time":99790,"text":"sat down,"},{"time":101717,"text":"took Harold's hand,"},{"time":103935,"text":"took his wife's hand"},{"time":106142,"text":"and just breathed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":108500,"text":"He said, \"It's not good\nnews is it, sonny?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":111132,"text":"I said, \"No.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":112564,"text":"And so we talked\nand we listened and we shared."},{"time":116867,"text":"And after a while I said,"},{"time":118124,"text":"\"Harold, what is it\nthat has meaning to you?"},{"time":121373,"text":"What is it that you hold sacred?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":123026,"text":"And he said,"},{"time":124365,"text":"\"My family.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":126525,"text":"I said, \"What do you want to do?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":128570,"text":"He slapped me on the knee\nand said, \"I want to go fishing.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":131761,"text":"I said, \"That, I know how to do.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":134646,"text":"Harold went fishing the next day."},{"time":137760,"text":"He died a week later."}]},{"cues":[{"time":140455,"text":"As I've gone through\nmy training in my career,"},{"time":143098,"text":"I think back to Harold."},{"time":144609,"text":"And I think that this is a conversation"},{"time":148782,"text":"that happens far too infrequently."},{"time":151737,"text":"And it's a conversation\nthat had led us to crisis,"},{"time":156173,"text":"to the biggest threat\nto the American way of life today,"},{"time":158861,"text":"which is health care expenditures."}]},{"cues":[{"time":161926,"text":"So what do we know?"},{"time":163127,"text":"We know that\nthis population, the most ill,"},{"time":166080,"text":"takes up 15 percent\nof the gross domestic product --"},{"time":168688,"text":"nearly 2.3 trillion dollars."},{"time":172307,"text":"So the sickest 15 percent\ntake up 15 percent of the GDP."},{"time":175891,"text":"If we extrapolate this out\nover the next two decades"},{"time":179755,"text":"with the growth of baby boomers,"},{"time":182838,"text":"at this rate it is 60 percent of the GDP."},{"time":188177,"text":"Sixty percent of the gross\ndomestic product"},{"time":190480,"text":"of the United States of America --"},{"time":192128,"text":"it has very little to do\nwith health care at that point."},{"time":195148,"text":"It has to do with a gallon of milk,"},{"time":197540,"text":"with college tuition."},{"time":199625,"text":"It has to do with\nevery thing that we value"},{"time":202112,"text":"and every thing that we know presently."},{"time":206514,"text":"It has at stake the free-market\neconomy and capitalism"},{"time":210729,"text":"of the United States of America."}]},{"cues":[{"time":214965,"text":"Let's forget all the statistics\nfor a minute, forget the numbers."},{"time":218145,"text":"Let's talk about the value we get\nfor all these dollars we spend."},{"time":222822,"text":"Well, the Dartmouth Atlas,\nabout six years ago,"},{"time":225439,"text":"looked at every dollar\nspent by Medicare --"},{"time":228216,"text":"generally this population."},{"time":229851,"text":"We found that those patients who have\nthe highest per capita expenditures"},{"time":236050,"text":"had the highest suffering,\npain, depression."},{"time":240182,"text":"And, more often than not, they die sooner."}]},{"cues":[{"time":243824,"text":"How can this be?"},{"time":245789,"text":"We live in the United States,"},{"time":247217,"text":"it has the greatest health care\nsystem on the planet."},{"time":249731,"text":"We spend 10 times more on these patients"},{"time":252260,"text":"than the second-leading\ncountry in the world."},{"time":255196,"text":"That doesn't make sense."},{"time":257764,"text":"But what we know is,"},{"time":259147,"text":"out of the top 50 countries on the planet"},{"time":262342,"text":"with organized health care systems,"},{"time":265949,"text":"we rank 37th."},{"time":270017,"text":"Former Eastern Bloc countries\nand sub-Saharan African countries"},{"time":274327,"text":"rank higher than us\nas far as quality and value."}]},{"cues":[{"time":280485,"text":"Something I experience\nevery day in my practice,"},{"time":283047,"text":"and I'm sure, something many of you\non your own journeys have experienced:"},{"time":287927,"text":"more is not more."},{"time":292196,"text":"Those individuals who had more tests,"},{"time":294209,"text":"more bells, more whistles,"},{"time":295503,"text":"more chemotherapy,\nmore surgery, more whatever --"},{"time":297955,"text":"the more that we do to someone,"},{"time":301283,"text":"it decreases the quality of their life."},{"time":305422,"text":"And it shortens it, most often."}]},{"cues":[{"time":309896,"text":"So what are we going to do about this?"},{"time":311745,"text":"What are we doing about this?"},{"time":313461,"text":"And why is this so?"},{"time":315097,"text":"The grim reality, ladies and gentlemen,"},{"time":317025,"text":"is that we, the health care industry --\nlong white-coat physicians --"},{"time":320447,"text":"are stealing from you."},{"time":322877,"text":"Stealing from you the opportunity"},{"time":325974,"text":"to choose how you want to live your lives"},{"time":328358,"text":"in the context of whatever disease it is."},{"time":330863,"text":"We focus on disease\nand pathology and surgery"},{"time":333656,"text":"and pharmacology."},{"time":337319,"text":"We miss the human being."},{"time":341434,"text":"How can we treat this"},{"time":342985,"text":"without understanding this?"},{"time":347029,"text":"We do things to this;"},{"time":350948,"text":"we need to do things for this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":356161,"text":"The triple aim of healthcare:"},{"time":357965,"text":"one, improve patient experience."},{"time":361081,"text":"Two, improve the population health."},{"time":365467,"text":"Three, decrease per capita expenditure\nacross a continuum."},{"time":371591,"text":"Our group, palliative care,"},{"time":373358,"text":"in 2012, working with\nthe sickest of the sick --"},{"time":379000,"text":"cancer,"},{"time":380175,"text":"heart disease, lung disease,"},{"time":382017,"text":"renal disease,"},{"time":383192,"text":"dementia --"},{"time":385681,"text":"how did we improve patient experience?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":389010,"text":"\"I want to be at home, Doc.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":390633,"text":"\"OK, we'll bring the care to you.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":392868,"text":"Quality of life, enhanced."},{"time":395732,"text":"Think about the human being."}]},{"cues":[{"time":397114,"text":"Two: population health."},{"time":399069,"text":"How did we look\nat this population differently,"},{"time":401944,"text":"and engage with them\nat a different level, a deeper level,"},{"time":404816,"text":"and connect to a broader sense\nof the human condition than my own?"},{"time":409091,"text":"How do we manage this group,"},{"time":412584,"text":"so that of our outpatient population,"},{"time":414377,"text":"94 percent, in 2012,\nnever had to go to the hospital?"},{"time":419919,"text":"Not because they couldn't."},{"time":423213,"text":"But they didn't have to."},{"time":425022,"text":"We brought the care to them."},{"time":427356,"text":"We maintained their value, their quality."}]},{"cues":[{"time":433220,"text":"Number three: per capita expenditures."},{"time":436746,"text":"For this population,"},{"time":438168,"text":"that today is 2.3 trillion dollars\nand in 20 years is 60 percent of the GDP,"},{"time":443245,"text":"we reduced health care expenditures\nby nearly 70 percent."},{"time":448873,"text":"They got more of what they wanted\nbased on their values,"},{"time":452346,"text":"lived better and are living longer,"},{"time":455464,"text":"for two-thirds less money."}]},{"cues":[{"time":462880,"text":"While Harold's time was limited,"},{"time":465663,"text":"palliative care's is not."},{"time":468288,"text":"Palliative care is a paradigm\nfrom diagnosis through the end of life."},{"time":474677,"text":"The hours,"},{"time":476361,"text":"weeks, months, years,"},{"time":479916,"text":"across a continuum --"},{"time":481098,"text":"with treatment, without treatment."}]},{"cues":[{"time":483006,"text":"Meet Christine."},{"time":485196,"text":"Stage III cervical cancer,"},{"time":487151,"text":"so, metastatic cancer\nthat started in her cervix,"},{"time":490196,"text":"spread throughout her body."},{"time":492719,"text":"She's in her 50s and she is living."},{"time":496743,"text":"This is not about end of life,"},{"time":498360,"text":"this is about life."},{"time":501180,"text":"This is not just about the elderly,"},{"time":503094,"text":"this is about people."}]},{"cues":[{"time":505929,"text":"This is Richard."},{"time":507706,"text":"End-stage lung disease."}]},{"cues":[{"time":510427,"text":"\"Richard, what is it\nthat you hold sacred?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":513581,"text":"\"My kids, my wife and my Harley.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":517094,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":518129,"text":"\"Alright!"},{"time":520544,"text":"I can't drive you around on it\nbecause I can barely pedal a bicycle,"},{"time":523806,"text":"but let's see what we can do.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":526385,"text":"Richard came to me,"},{"time":528946,"text":"and he was in rough shape."},{"time":532444,"text":"He had this little voice telling him"},{"time":534249,"text":"that maybe his time was weeks to months."},{"time":537488,"text":"And then we just talked."},{"time":538778,"text":"And I listened and tried to hear --"},{"time":542891,"text":"big difference."},{"time":544202,"text":"Use these in proportion to this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":548479,"text":"I said, \"Alright, let's take it\none day at a time,\""},{"time":551028,"text":"like we do in every\nother chapter of our life."},{"time":554573,"text":"And we have met Richard\nwhere Richard's at day-to-day."},{"time":559006,"text":"And it's a phone call or two a week,"},{"time":563059,"text":"but he's thriving in the context\nof end-stage lung disease."}]},{"cues":[{"time":571040,"text":"Now, palliative medicine is not\njust for the elderly,"},{"time":573557,"text":"it is not just for the middle-aged."},{"time":577535,"text":"It is for everyone."}]},{"cues":[{"time":579090,"text":"Meet my friend Jonathan."},{"time":581903,"text":"We have the honor and pleasure"},{"time":583407,"text":"of Jonathan and his father\njoining us here today."},{"time":585751,"text":"Jonathan is in his 20s,\nand I met him several years ago."},{"time":588607,"text":"He was dealing with\nmetastatic testicular cancer,"},{"time":592700,"text":"spread to his brain."},{"time":594465,"text":"He had a stroke,"},{"time":596375,"text":"he had brain surgery,"},{"time":597947,"text":"radiation, chemotherapy."},{"time":601579,"text":"Upon meeting him and his family,"},{"time":603399,"text":"he was a couple of weeks away\nfrom a bone marrow transplant,"},{"time":606254,"text":"and in listening and engaging,"},{"time":608539,"text":"they said, \"Help us\nunderstand -- what is cancer?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":615764,"text":"How did we get this far"},{"time":618513,"text":"without understanding\nwhat we're dealing with?"},{"time":621276,"text":"How did we get this far\nwithout empowering somebody"},{"time":623714,"text":"to know what it is they're dealing with,"},{"time":625650,"text":"and then taking the next step and engaging\nin who they are as human beings"},{"time":629282,"text":"to know if that is what we should do?"},{"time":631402,"text":"Lord knows we can do\nany kind of thing to you."},{"time":637133,"text":"But should we?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":641870,"text":"And don't take my word for it."},{"time":643578,"text":"All the evidence that is related\nto palliative care these days"},{"time":648054,"text":"demonstrates with absolute certainty\npeople live better and live longer."},{"time":652199,"text":"There was a seminal article\nout of the New England Journal of Medicine"},{"time":655567,"text":"in 2010."},{"time":657621,"text":"A study done at Harvard\nby friends of mine, colleagues."},{"time":660309,"text":"End-stage lung cancer:"},{"time":661714,"text":"one group with palliative care,"},{"time":664695,"text":"a similar group without."},{"time":667782,"text":"The group with palliative care\nreported less pain,"},{"time":671901,"text":"less depression."},{"time":673556,"text":"They needed fewer hospitalizations."},{"time":676487,"text":"And, ladies and gentlemen,"},{"time":678639,"text":"they lived three to six months longer."},{"time":683805,"text":"If palliative care were a cancer drug,"},{"time":687867,"text":"every cancer doctor on the planet\nwould write a prescription for it."},{"time":692845,"text":"Why don't they?"},{"time":695570,"text":"Again, because we goofy,\nlong white-coat physicians"},{"time":698938,"text":"are trained and of the mantra\nof dealing with this,"},{"time":704401,"text":"not with this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":710697,"text":"This is a space that we will\nall come to at some point."},{"time":715709,"text":"But this conversation today\nis not about dying,"},{"time":718457,"text":"it is about living."},{"time":720289,"text":"Living based on our values,"},{"time":721637,"text":"what we find sacred"},{"time":723080,"text":"and how we want to write\nthe chapters of our lives,"},{"time":725521,"text":"whether it's the last"},{"time":727379,"text":"or the last five."},{"time":730258,"text":"What we know,"},{"time":732277,"text":"what we have proven,"},{"time":734475,"text":"is that this conversation\nneeds to happen today --"},{"time":737946,"text":"not next week, not next year."},{"time":740029,"text":"What is at stake is our lives today"},{"time":742883,"text":"and the lives of us as we get older"},{"time":744707,"text":"and the lives of our children\nand our grandchildren."},{"time":748310,"text":"Not just in that hospital room"},{"time":750207,"text":"or on the couch at home,"},{"time":752141,"text":"but everywhere we go\nand everything we see."},{"time":756326,"text":"Palliative medicine is the answer\nto engage with human beings,"},{"time":761570,"text":"to change the journey\nthat we will all face,"},{"time":766304,"text":"and change it for the better."}]},{"cues":[{"time":770148,"text":"To my colleagues,"},{"time":772823,"text":"to my patients,"},{"time":774702,"text":"to my government,"},{"time":776303,"text":"to all human beings,"},{"time":778386,"text":"I ask that we stand and we\nshout and we demand"},{"time":782641,"text":"the best care possible,"},{"time":785352,"text":"so that we can live better today"},{"time":787606,"text":"and ensure a better life tomorrow."},{"time":789311,"text":"We need to shift today"},{"time":792452,"text":"so that we can live tomorrow."}]},{"cues":[{"time":796838,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":798013,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}